---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog • Portfolio">
  <section class="section">
    <h1>technical blog.</h1>
    <p>
      thoughts on frontend development, performance optimization, 
      and the evolving landscape of web technologies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <article class="blog-post">
      <div class="blog-meta">december 15, 2024</div>
      <h2 class="blog-title">optimizing react performance with concurrent features</h2>
      <p class="blog-excerpt">
        exploring how react 18's concurrent features can dramatically improve user experience 
        in data-heavy applications. practical examples and performance measurements included.
      </p>
      <a href="#" class="read-more">read more →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-post">
      <div class="blog-meta">november 28, 2024</div>
      <h2 class="blog-title">building accessible components with compound patterns</h2>
      <p class="blog-excerpt">
        deep dive into creating reusable, accessible react components using compound component patterns. 
        includes keyboard navigation, screen reader support, and focus management.
      </p>
      <a href="#" class="read-more">read more →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-post">
      <div class="blog-meta">october 22, 2024</div>
      <h2 class="blog-title">micro-frontends: architecture decisions and tradeoffs</h2>
      <p class="blog-excerpt">
        lessons learned from implementing micro-frontend architecture at scale. 
        covering module federation, shared dependencies, and team coordination strategies.
      </p>
      <a href="#" class="read-more">read more →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-post">
      <div class="blog-meta">september 10, 2024</div>
      <h2 class="blog-title">css container queries: the responsive design revolution</h2>
      <p class="blog-excerpt">
        how container queries are changing the way we think about responsive design. 
        practical examples and browser support considerations for modern web applications.
      </p>
      <a href="#" class="read-more">read more →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-post">
      <div class="blog-meta">august 5, 2024</div>
      <h2 class="blog-title">typescript patterns for better react development</h2>
      <p class="blog-excerpt">
        advanced typescript patterns that improve developer experience and code quality in react applications. 
        covering generic components, discriminated unions, and type-safe patterns.
      </p>
      <a href="#" class="read-more">read more →</a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>topics i write about</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      frontend architecture • performance optimization • accessibility • typescript • react patterns • 
      build tools • testing strategies • developer experience • web standards
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
